author: Dan Duggan | NJ Advance Media for NJ.com
title: NJ.com's Week 5 Big Ten power rankings: Is Northwestern on top?
text:
Comments 
The national polls continue to show deference to Ohio State and Michigan State over Northwestern for reasons unknown. 
Aside from a higher preseason ranking and more hype, the Buckeyes and Spartans haven't done anything to demonstrate superiority over the Wildcats. All three teams are 5-0, but Northwestern has more quality wins (Stanford, at Duke, Minnesota) and, with the top defense in the nation, has been more impressive. 
That resume has the Wildcats at No. 13 in the AP poll . Meanwhile, No. 1 Ohio State, which barely held off an Indiana team that lost its quarterback and running back to injuries, and No. 4 Michigan State, which had to hang on for a three-point win over lowly Purdue, maintained their spot near the top of the national rankings. 
The first weekend of Big Ten football was full of defensive struggles and nasty weather that led to some ugly games. A pair of West Division matchups took center stage. Northwestern blanked Minnesota, 27-0, and Iowa out-slugged Wisconsin, 10-6, to move ahead early in the division race.
